The aim of the course is to introduce students with the basic principles of scientific research: how to make the research plan, how to set the resrearch problem and formulate the research tasks and present the results. The output of the course is small pilot research. The students are expected to:
1. work independently
2. participate in seminars that take place about once a month and address main components of academic writing and scientific research. 
3. take part of supervision-seminars (details and schedule according to agreement with one's supervisor).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce students with the basic principles of scientific research: how to make the research plan, how to set the resrearch problem and formulate the research tasks and present the results. The output of the course is small pilot research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student will: - know how to find relevant literature - be able to place their research into wider theoretical framework - be able to choose appropriate research method(s) for their study - plan and carry out (small pilot research) their original study - know  the main rules for referencing others' work - justify choices made in the research process and defend their work.
